Q: How can you achieve to make it only woks when it is not in the mobile mode?
.lightbox img {
  max-width: 500px !important;
  height: auto !important;
  display: block !important;
  margin-left: auto !important;
  margin-right: auto !important;
}
It worked to change the default size in Quarto websites. Thank you very much for telling me how to achieve it.
But now I noticed that it breaks when it comes the mobile mode. How can you achieve to make it only woks when it is not in the mobile mode?


A:You can restrict the CSS rule to apply only on larger screens (non-mobile mode) by using a media query.
You can restrict the CSS rule to apply only on larger screens(non-mobile mode) by using a media query. Here‚Äôs how to modify yourCSS:
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .lightbox img {
    max-width: 500px !important;
    height: auto !important;
    display: block !important;
    margin-left: auto !important;
    margin-right: auto !important;
  }
}

‚úÖ What this does:

The styles inside @media (min-width: 768px) will only apply whenthe screen width is 768 pixels or larger (i.e., tablets anddesktops).
On mobile devices (narrower than 768px), the image will use thedefault lightbox styles, which are typically responsive and smaller.

You can adjust 768px to match your design breakpoint if needed (e.g.,640px, 1024px, etc.).



